# 🛠️ Installation & Setup Guide for N-PLAYER

Welcome to the setup guide for **N-PLAYER**. Follow these instructions to get the local development environment running smoothly on your machine.

## 📋 Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed on your system:
* **Node.js** (v14.0 or higher recommended) - [Download here](https://nodejs.org/)
* **Git** (optional, for cloning the repository)

## 🚀 Step-by-Step Installation

### 1. Clone the Repository
If you haven't already, clone this repository to your local machine and navigate into the project directory:
```bash
git clone [https://github.com/Akkiplayon/N-PLAYER.git](https://github.com/Akkiplayon/N-PLAYER.git)
cd N-PLAYER
2. Install Dependencies
This project uses Node.js modules for backend and build processes. Run the following command in your terminal to install all required dependencies:

Bash
npm install
3. FFmpeg & Executables Configuration
N-PLAYER requires FFmpeg for media processing and streaming functionalities.

No external installation is required. All necessary executable files, including ffmpeg.exe, are already bundled within the /bin directory of this repository.

The application is pre-configured to automatically locate and utilize these binaries from the /bin path.

4. Assets
All static assets (images, icons, UI elements) are pre-loaded and organized in their respective directories. You do not need to configure them manually.

5. Run the Application
Once all dependencies are installed, you can start the local development server by running:

Bash
npm start
(The application should now be accessible via your local host in the web browser.)
Your directory structure should look exactly like this before you start the app:
```text
N-PLAYER/
├── bin/
│   ├── ffmpeg.exe
│   └── ffprobe.exe
├── assets/
├── sample/
├── construction_plane/
├── index.html
└── ... 
